description:
"""h3. Issue Summary    When a Jira issue is added to a Confluence page, a remote link of *mentioned in* is created in Jira. Though, sometimes this link is not created. The issue is intermittent and doesn't happen all the time.    h3. Steps to Reproduce  # Install Confluence v7.4  # Integrate it with Jira  # Add a Jira issue to a page    h3. Expected Results    Jira issue should have a *mentioned in* link   !works-1.png|thumbnail!     In the above snapshot, the issue *WOR-18* is mentioned in a page *adding some text*. The page appears under *mentioned in* on Jira side    h3. Actual Results    Jira issue doesn't have the *mentioned in* link.      !doesnot-1.png|thumbnail!     Issue *WOR-17* doesn't have a corresponding link for page *adding some text*    This issue is intermittent, happens sometimes and works other times.      h3. *Notes*    Confluence sends an HTTP POST to Jira to create remote links.  {code:title=org.apache.http DEBUG logs}  2020-07-24 14:36:48,412 DEBUG [Jira remote link executor:thread-26] [org.apache.http.wire] wire http-outgoing-739 >> """"POST /j822/rest/api/latest/issue/WOR-18/remotelink HTTP/1.1[][
]""""  .  2020-07-24 14:36:48,413 DEBUG [Jira remote link executor:thread-26] [org.apache.http.wire] wire http-outgoing-739 >> """"Host: jiraonlocal:8080[][
]""""  .  2020-07-24 14:36:48,414 DEBUG [Jira remote link executor:thread-26] [org.apache.http.wire] wire http-outgoing-739 >> """"{""""application"""":{""""name"""":""""Confluence"""",""""type"""":""""com.atlassian.confluence""""},""""globalId"""":""""appId=9d17e0bd-ab19-33a3-95bb-66b39577cde6&pageId=6422540"""",""""relationship"""":""""mentioned in"""",""""object"""":{""""title"""":""""Page"""",""""url"""":""""https://website.com:9443/c6154/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=6422540""""}}""""  .  2020-07-24 14:36:48,578 DEBUG [Jira remote link executor:thread-26] [org.apache.http.wire] wire http-outgoing-739 << """"HTTP/1.1 201 [][
]""""  {code}    Where remote link is not created in Jira, the above logging is not seen in Confluence.     h3. Workaround    Remove the Jira issue from the page in Confluence and add it again."""
